Making Cross-Framework compatible models.¶

A guide to convert arcgis.learn PyTorch models to Tensorflow via Onnx¶

Who's the GOAT (Greatest of all time)?

The never ending debate of supremacy¶

  • Messi or Ronaldo

  • Kobe or Jordan

  • Marvel or DC

Tensorflow or PyTorch

STOP the war !!¶

We can't decide on who is better between Messi and Ronaldo or Kobe and Jordan. But we can enjoy watching them both and similarly we can enjoy the best of both Tensorflow and Pytorch worlds using Onnx. To reiterate, you can

  • Build your model in PyTorch and deploy on Tensorflow

  • Train your model in Tensorflow and perform inference on PyTorch

All you need is a pinch of ONNX!!¶

What is ONNX?¶

ONNX stands for Open Neural Network Exchange. ONNX is an open format to represent deep learning models. With ONNX, AI developers can more easily move models between state-of-the-art tools and choose the combination that is best for them.

More about ONNX at https://onnx.ai/

Why do we need Tensorflow¶

Because we are User centric¶

Tensorflow is the clear winner when it comes to deployment¶

This is how we do it¶

In [1]:
# Imports 

from arcgis.learn import SingleShotDetector, prepare_data
In [2]:
# Prepare Data and Model

data_path = r'C:\Projects\Office work\Cross_platform_mobility\data\good_pool'

data = prepare_data(data_path,batch_size=16, val_split_pct=0.5)

ssd_model = SingleShotDetector(data, grids=[4],zooms=[1.0],ratios=[[1.0,1.0]])
In [ ]:
# Fit model to data and save it

ssd_model.fit(epochs=100, lr=0.0012)

ssd_model.save('ssd_model')
In [4]:
# Load the model

ssd_model.load(r'C:\Projects\Office work\Cross_platform_mobility\data\good_pool\models\ssd_model')

Convert model to TF-ONNX format¶

  • Load a pretrained model
  • Generate a new model by training.

Then,¶

  • Call model.save with a parameter framework="tf=onnx"
  • batch_size is an optional parameter that can be given to the model.save function. By default batch_size=16
In [7]:
ssd_model.save('ssd_onnx', framework='tf-onnx')
Out[7]:
WindowsPath('C:/Projects/Office work/Cross_platform_mobility/data/good_pool/models/ssd_onnx')

Here are the generated model files¶

What did we do just now?¶

  • We saved our model as ONNX model file.
  • Internally we convert this ONNX model to Tensorflow GraphRep object.
  • Tensorflow GraphRep object can be used to perform inference on Tensorflow.

Let's go Pro¶
